# College Decision Doc Formatting Rules

These rules apply to `README.md` (the primary decision doc — was named `decision.md` before being renamed) and `background.md`. Gary has asked for these **repeatedly** — treat them as hard requirements, not style preferences.

## 1. Table cells with ratings/amounts MUST have `<br>` after the bolded lead

Every cell in the main comparison table's **Engineering Reputation**, **Rowing Culture Fit**, **Cost**, and **Risk** columns must follow this pattern (the column header is `Cost` — was renamed from `Tuition Cost` when the model switched to tuition + R&B):

```
**<Rating or amount>.**<br><supporting detail>
```

### Examples

GOOD:

```
| **1. WPI** | **Strong.**<br>#64 ranked engineering. ABET BS from day one. |
```

BAD (no line break — the rating runs into the supporting text):

```
| **1. WPI** | **Strong.** #64 ranked engineering. ABET BS from day one. |
```

**When you edit any cell in these four columns — including a tiny edit — re-verify the `<br>` is still there afterward.** Do not strip it. Do not "clean up" the table to remove `<br>` tags. Gary has asked three separate times to fix this after regressions; please don't make him ask a fourth.

### Mechanical check — RUN THIS after every table edit

After any edit that touches the comparison table, run:

```
./scripts/check-table-format.sh README.md
```

It exits 0 on success and prints the exact offending row + column on failure. A pre-commit hook at `.git/hooks/pre-commit` runs the same check on staged changes, so a bad commit gets blocked automatically — but running it inline catches regressions before they compound into a multi-edit mess. **Counting `<br>` tags with `grep -c` is NOT sufficient** and has produced false "all good" reports in the past; always use the validator script.

## 2. Option numbering is fixed — don't re-invent it

The current numbering is:

| # | Option |
